Kiambu government will set up a solid waste recycling plant to manage disposal.Environment executive Esther Njuguna said the plant will serve Kiambu, Thika and Limuru. She spoke on Wednesday at Gioto, the county&rsquo;s second largest dumpsite. &ldquo;Every day people produce garbage which is dumped at this site,&rdquo; she said.Njuguna said the plant will also provide jobs for the youth. Kiambu residents have been complaining about smoke when the garbage is burnt.They will hold a peaceful demonstration on Monday to press the county to move the dumpsite away from residential areas. Resident David Mwaniki said, &ldquo;On Sunday, the Catholic and PCEA churches could not hold services because of the stench and smoke from the site.&rdquo;